// Classroom scoping SPEC — who gets what scope, and why. No longer loaded by
// any binary (2026-07-08): scoping moved from hubd's Rust /ws relay to
// Mosquitto's own ACL, so this file's role changed from runtime config to
// human-readable intent. mosquitto-acl.example.conf + the passwd seed in
// deploy/install.sh are the mechanical implementation — keep them in sync on
// touch, same split as hub-zenoh's protocol/README (contract) vs
// zenoh-acl.example.json5 (enforcement).
//
// One credential total (confirmed 2026-07-13): the hub's own Wi-Fi is the
// classroom's real boundary, not a login — every robot and browser gets
// full read+write on robots/# with no credential at all (mosquitto-acl.
// example.conf's top-level rules). professor is the one exception, gated
// because it's the only thing that ACL can't give away for free: writing
// fleet/estop (CONTRACT.md § Fleet e-stop).
{
  professor: { username: "professor", password: "change-me" },
}
